column5: Something ive been toying around with in my CAD programs  Machining it would be a whole different story.
Now your just teasing me.  Nicely done.  I would ask the guys in the engineering room to design one,but were so frigg,n busy.  If you market that,let me know.LOL
Be nice as rims on my ford:lol:.
lmao, you got me interested in doodling again
Modeled in Autodesk Inventor, and rendered in Studio
You get them made , Im in for two .
Stop doodling,and make.LOL  That is a sweet design.
I was going to say.  That background image in the mirrors sure looks like Inventor to me.  Are you a CAD jockey?

making the parts would be the easy task.  finishing it to make it look that nice will triple the price.  hours upon hours of de-burring, polishing, plating/anodizing/masking installation. .........only to find out that some tolerances are out by a few microns.   does that not look like a car rim?
I have a table fan at the cottage that looks just like that
That's some pretty slick designing there!!!
Welcome to the center pin club ,,,,,,,,,,,,  :rofl2:
can you provide spec's? maybe I can machine it
I am indeed lol. And yep u can see the telltale autodesk parking lot reflection in the center nut of the reel
Everything is modeled except the "spoke" section of the reel, which is a wheel design decaled onto the model
Looks like something you'd find on an Escalade
I should send him a pic of your left rear rim Bill. That would be a nice reel design.  :rofl2:

If autocad has parametric 3d capabilities, it would be news to me. I rarely launch autocad anymore lol. Modeling was all inventor.  However with my premium suite license I get all kinds of add ons I'm excited about. 3dsmax being one of them.  Ive done some work with solid works here and there.....nice program
Um, do you have anything by Cragar, or maybe an old-school spoke look?
Cragar....lol, how 70's
lol, how 60s! But a pretty enduring design, I think.
